The article is a message and notice from President Barack Obama on the continuation of the national emergency with respect to Syria. The President states that the actions and policies of the Syrian government, including support for terrorist organizations and pursuit of weapons of mass destruction and missile programs, pose a continuing threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. The President has determined that it is necessary to continue the national emergency and maintain sanctions to address this threat. The United States also condemns the use of violence against peaceful demonstrators in Syria and calls on the Syrian government to respect human rights and work towards greater freedom, democracy, opportunity, and justice. The President will consider changes in the policies and actions of the Syrian government in determining whether to continue or terminate the national emergency in the future.